Good Governance Ambassadors of Nigeria (GOGAN) is a non-governmental organization (NGO) founded by Chief Felix Idiga, the Chairman/National Coordinator. The organization is made up of patriotic Nigerians who are committed to advocacy for good governance, rule of law and adherence to democratic ethosGood Governance Ambassadors of Nigeria (GOGAN) identifies office holders who are models of good governance for special commendation and encouragement.Good Governance Ambassadors of Nigeria (GOGAN) is committed to the promotion of peace, unity mutual understanding and genuine reconciliation among party members and more importantly to cooperate with the party leadership at ensuring strict implementation of the party manifesto by political office holders across all levels by encouraging performance through awards and commendations.In 2018, Good Governance Ambassadors of Nigeria (GOGAN) announced its essay writing competition for Nigerians. The nationwide competition brought together Nigerians from all over in an intellectual bout that challenges them to develop smart solutions and unleash hidden potentials that will project good leadership in the country.Good Governance Ambassadors of Nigeria (GOGAN) promotes the interest of Nigerians in terms of ensuring satisfactory fulfillment of campaign promises made by politicians.


